  "prompt": "In reaction, [math]N_2 O_4\\to {2NO_2}_{(g)}[/math], what will be the value of [math]K_C[/math] at 35\u00b0 C if [math]N_2 O_4[/math] is dissociated to the extent of 20% under a pressure of 1 atmosphere?",
  "response": "To determine the equilibrium constant \\( K_C \\) for the reaction \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\rightleftharpoons 2\\text{NO}_2 \\) at 35\u00b0C, given that \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) is 20% dissociated under a pressure of 1 atmosphere, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Define the Degree of Dissociation\nLet the degree of dissociation be \\( \\alpha = 0.20 \\).\n\n### Step 2: Initial and Equilibrium Moles\nAssume we start with 1 mole of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\).\n\nAt equilibrium:\n- Moles of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) dissociated = \\( \\alpha \\)\n- Moles of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) remaining = \\( 1 - \\alpha \\)\n- Moles of \\( \\text{NO}_2 \\) formed = \\( 2\\alpha \\)\n\nTotal moles at equilibrium:\n\\[ n_{\\text{total}} = (1 - \\alpha) + 2\\alpha = 1 + \\alpha \\]\n\n### Step 3: Partial Pressures\nGiven the total pressure \\( P = 1 \\) atm, the partial pressures are:\n\\[ P_{\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4} = \\frac{1 - \\alpha}{1 + \\alpha}P \\]\n\\[ P_{\\text{NO}_2} = \\frac{2\\alpha}{1 + \\alpha}P \\]\n\nSubstitute \\( P = 1 \\) atm and \\( \\alpha = 0.20 \\):\n\\[ P_{\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4} = \\frac{1 - 0.20}{1 + 0.20}(1) = \\frac{0.80}{1.20} = \\frac{2}{3} \\text{ atm} \\]\n\\[ P_{\\text{NO}_2} = \\frac{2 \\times 0.20}{1.20}(1) = \\frac{0.40}{1.20} = \\frac{1}{3} \\text{ atm} \\]\n\n### Step 4: Equilibrium Constant in Terms of Pressure (\\( K_P \\))\n\\[ K_P = \\frac{(P_{\\text{NO}_2})^2}{P_{\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4}}} \\]\n\\[ K_P = \\frac{\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^2}{\\frac{2}{3}} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{9}}{\\frac{2}{3}} = \\frac{1}{6} \\]\n\n### Step 5: Relate \\( K_P \\) to \\( K_C \\)\nThe relationship between \\( K_P \\) and \\( K_C \\) is:\n\\[ K_P = K_C(RT)^{\\Delta n} \\]\nwhere:\n- \\( R = 0.0821 \\) L\u00b7atm\u00b7K\u207b\u00b9\u00b7mol\u207b\u00b9\n- \\( T = 35^\\circ \\text{C} = 308 \\) K\n- \\( \\Delta n = 2 - 1 = 1 \\)\n\n\\[ K_P = K_C(RT)^1 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{1}{6} = K_C(0.0821 \\times 308) \\]\n\\[ K_C = \\frac{1}{6 \\times 25.2658} \\]\n\\[ K_C \\approx 0.0066 \\]\n\n### Final Answer\n\\[ K_C \\approx 0.0066 \\]",
  "temperature": 1.0,
